  <!-- Process Section -->
  <ProcessSection 
    serviceType="acquisition-finance"
    title="Securing Acquisition Finance Made Simple"
    description="Our structured approach ensures you have the right finance structure for successful business acquisitions."
    disclaimer="Acquisition finance subject to business valuation, due diligence requirements, and credit assessment. Terms vary based on transaction structure and risk profile."
  />

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6 font-['Instrument_Sans'] text-[#1C2C3B]">
            Frequently Asked Questions
          </h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white shadow-md">
            <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex justify-between items-center faq-toggle">
              <span class="font-semibold text-[#1C2C3B]">What types of businesses can be financed for acquisition?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
              <p class="text-gray-600">Most established businesses with proven cash flow and trading history can be financed. We specialise in trades businesses but can arrange finance for manufacturing, and other commercial enterprises. The key factors are business stability, tangible asset base, profitability, and strategic business fit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white shadow-md">
            <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex justify-between items-center faq-toggle">
              <span class="font-semibold text-[#1C2C3B]">How much of the purchase price can be financed?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
              <p class="text-gray-600">This can vary widely based on the specifics of the deal. Typically 50-60% of the purchase price can be financed, depending on the business type, assets, and cash flow. Some acquisitions may qualify for higher percentages depending on the strength of the deal. We'll work with you to optimise the finance structure.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white shadow-md">
            <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex justify-between items-center faq-toggle">
              <span class="font-semibold text-[#1C2C3B]">What due diligence is required for acquisition finance?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
              <p class="text-gray-600">Due diligence typically includes detailed financial analysis, business valuation, business planning and strategic fit, legal review, and market analysis. The level of scutiny depends on the transaction size and complexity. We will manage this with you throughout the process</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white shadow-md">
            <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex justify-between items-center faq-toggle">
              <span class="font-semibold text-[#1C2C3B]">How long does the acquisition finance process take?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
              <p class="text-gray-600">The timeline varies based on transaction complexity and due diligence requirements. Simple acquisitions may settle within 4-6 weeks, while complex deals can take 8-12 weeks. We work to match the finance timeline to your purchase contract requirements wherever possible. Be aware these deals are typically much more involved than a normal business application, so can take longer.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white shadow-md">
            <button class="w-full px-6 py-4 text-left flex justify-between items-center faq-toggle">
              <span class="font-semibold text-[#1C2C3B]">What security is required for acquisition finance?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div class="hidden px-6 pb-4">
              <p class="text-gray-600">Security typically includes General Security Agreements over the business being acquired and its assets and Personal Guarantees from Directors and major Shareholders. Additional security may include property, other business assets, or corporate guarantees from other trading entities depending on the deal structure and risk assessment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Newsletter CTA Section -->
  <NewsLetter />
